<title>JAPAN: Toyo Trust problem loans (Banking account).</title>
<headline>Toyo Trust problem loans (Banking account).</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-11-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Toyo Trust &amp; Banking Co Ltd has disclosed its restructured loans (in billions of yen unless specified):</p>
<p>					end-Sep 96     end-Mar 96</p>
<p>  Restructured loans	    12.01	   261.16</p>
<p>  Bad loans			100.59	     41.9</p>
<p>  Non-performing loans	   51.6	    55.32</p>
<p>  Loans to troubled clients	--	    47.98</p>
<p>  Total problem loans	   164.2	   406.36</p>
<p>Restructured loans are those on which interest rates have been cut to help corporate restructuring. Bad loans are to bankrupt firms and non-performing are those with interest payments in arrears by six months or more. Loans to troubled clients are mainly to the bank's non-bank affiliates.</p>
</text>
